@node OVER "ManiacManipulator Overview"

 short: with ManiacManipulator you can patch your saved games and get
        millions of credits...

 ManiacMan was made for the lazy people who don't want (or don't know
 how) to use a hex-editor like AZap, NewZap, Zaphod or similar.

 Imagine you play that rock-hard game and you're out of money again.
 Load ManiacMan and cheat your saved game. Life can be so easy...

 Since V2.0 ManiacMan now comes without an own GUI (Graphical User
 Interface). Instead of that AmigaGuide is used.


 WARNING!!!

 Make backups of your savegames before patching them for the first time.
 If one patch doesn't work (maybe you've got another version of the game)
 I don't want to receive any flames - they'll be ignored!

 WARNING!!!


 ManiacMan (the executable) is FREEWARE, so use and spread it like hell,
 but don't change the code or anything else.

 ManiacManipulator (the file you're reading) is SUPPORTWARE. If you like it
 and use it, please support it with sending either savegames or the Patches-
 file. If you decide to send savegames, please tell me how many money you've
 got in that game (else I can't find the adress where that value is stored).


@endnode

@node INST "ManiacManipulator Installation"

 Installation is easy, of course :)

 Move the ManiacMan-drawer wherever you want.

 That's it !


@endnode

@node USAG "ManiacManipulator Usage"

 After selecting the game you want to patch, a filerequester will appear,
 asking you for the file. Choose the savegame (often ends with .sav or
 can be found in a separate savegame-drawer) and all work will be done
 for you. Easy, isn't it?

 For those who want to write their own patches (everything is possible),
 I now made ManiacMan to be controlled by the commandline.

 For more information about that, start ManiacMan without options.


@endnode

@node CRED "ManiacManipulator Credits"

 Maniac Manipulator was written in ACE Basic V2.4 and compiled with
 PhxAss V4.34 using an Amiga1200 with OS3.1, 68040 CPU and 6MB RAM.

 Thanks to David Benn for ACE

