@node HILL "Hillsea Lido"

The savegames are stored in Hillsea Lido's -S- -drawer. The name is
xMSAV-3 where x is the save position (1MSAV-3 if you saved at position 1
by pressing F1).

@endnode

@node MECH "Mechforce"

This patch is for the full version. Robert Kawka told me that there are
different savegames. This one's for the single fighter saves (1032 bytes).

If you encounter problems, please contact Robert: roberto@santana.gun.de


@endnode

@node SWOS "Sensible World Of Soccer"

The parameter for the 95/96-version was taken from my old SWOSCheater.
I used to play in AGA mode and I don't know if there's a difference when
saving an ECS game...

Andreas Neumann told me that it doesn't work with his 96/97-version of
SWOS. He gave me the new parameter. It only differs 1 byte.

Please test which one works for you and let me know!

Savegames have the suffix .CAR


@endnode

@node SBII "Speedball II"

Speedball II saves a game to the bootblock of the savedisk. You'll have
to save the bootblock to a file (1024 bytes) to make use of this patch,
and write it back to the disk afterwards. There are many tools available
for this work (most virus-killers have an option to save the BB).

You might wonder why the money is 10240 Credits. Well, there was a little
problem of which I couldn't find the cause. But who cares? It works!


@endnode

@node UFOA "UFO - Enemy Unknown AGA"

This is for the old 4-disk-version of UFO. I don't think anything has
changed with the new 5-disk-version.

The file to alter is 'liglob.dat'


@endnode

